<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Monro is a chain of 1,029
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The predecessor to the Company was founded by Charles J. August in 1957 as a Midas Muffler franchise in Rochester, New York, specializing in mufflers and exhaust systems.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company was incorporated in the State of New York in 1959.&nbsp;&nbsp;In 1966, we discontinued our affiliation with Midas Muffler, and began to diversify into a full line of undercar repair services.&nbsp;&nbsp;An investor group led by Peter J. Solomon and Donald Glickman purchased a controlling interest in the Company in July 1984.&nbsp;&nbsp;At that time, Monro operated 59 stores, located primarily in upstate New York, with approximately $21 million in sales in fiscal 1984.&nbsp;&nbsp;Since 1984, we have continued our growth and have expanded our marketing area to include 24 additional states.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In December 1998, Monro appointed Robert G. Gross as President and Chief Executive Officer, who began full-time responsibilities on January 1, 1999.&nbsp;&nbsp;Effective October 1, 2012, Mr. Gross assumed the role of Executive Chairman and John W. Van Heel was appointed Chief Executive Officer.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company's principal executive offices are located at 200 Holleder Parkway, Rochester, New York 14615, and our telephone number is (585) 647-6400.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Monro provides a broad range of services on passenger cars, light trucks and vans for brakes; mufflers and exhaust systems; and steering, drive train, suspension and wheel alignment.&nbsp;&nbsp;Monro also provides other products and services, including tires and routine maintenance services, including state inspections.&nbsp;&nbsp;Monro specializes in the repair and replacement of parts which must be periodically replaced as they wear out.&nbsp;&nbsp;Normal wear on these parts generally is not covered by new car warranties.&nbsp;&nbsp;Monro typically does not perform under-the-hood repair services except for oil change services, various &#x201C;flush and fill&#x201D; services and some minor tune-up services.&nbsp;&nbsp;Monro does not sell parts or accessories to the do-it-yourself market.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	All of the Company&#x2019;s stores, except Tire Warehouse and Tire Barn Warehouse stores, provide the services described above.&nbsp;&nbsp;Tire Warehouse and Tire Barn Warehouse stores only sell tires and tire related services and alignments.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, a growing number of our stores are more specialized in tire replacement and service and, accordingly, have a higher mix of sales in the tire category.&nbsp;&nbsp;These stores are described below as tire stores, whereas the remaining stores are described as service stores.&nbsp;&nbsp;(See additional discussion under &#x201C;Operating Strategy&#x201D;.)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	At March 26, 2016, there were 515
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	stores de
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	signated as service stores and 514
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	as tire stores.
</FONT>
</P>

</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	On April 25, 2015, we acquired the Car-X
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	b
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	rand, as well as the franchise rights for 146 auto service centers from Car-X Associates Corp.&nbsp;&nbsp;(See additional discussion under Note 2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Consolidated Financial Statements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Car-X, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	operates as the franchisor through a standard royalty agreement, while Car-X remains a separate and independent brand and business with franchise operations based in Illinois.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s of March 26, 2016, Monro had 134
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Car-X franchised locations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	INDUSTRY OVERVIEW
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	According to industry reports, demand for automotive repair services, including undercar repair and tire services, has increased due to the general increase in the number of vehicles registered, the increase in the average age of vehicles and the increased complexity of vehicles, which makes it more difficult for a vehicle owner to perform do-it-yourself repairs.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	At the same time as demand for automotive repair services has grown, the number of general repair outlets has decreased, principally because fewer gas stations now perform repairs, and because there are fewer new car dealers as a result of dealership closures by car manufacturers, such as Chrysler and General Motors.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe that these factors present opportunities for increased sales by the Company, even though the number of specialized repair outlets (such as those operated by Monro and our direct competitors) has increased to meet growing demand.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	EXPANSION STRATEGY
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Monro has experienced significant growth in recent years due to acquisitions and, to a lesser extent, the opening of new stores.&nbsp;&nbsp;Management believes that the continued growth in sales and profits of the Company is dependent, in large part, upon our continued ability to open/acquire and operate new stores on a profitable basis.&nbsp;&nbsp;Overall profitability of the Company may not meet expectations if acquired or new stores do not attain expected profitability.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Monro believes that there are significant expansion opportunities in new as well as existing market areas, which may result from a combination of constructing stores on vacant land and acquiring existing store locations.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe that, as the industry consolidates due to the increasingly complex nature of automotive repair, the expanded capital requirements for state-of-the-art equipment and aging of existing shop owners, there will be increasing opportunities for acquisitions of existing businesses or store structures.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>

</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>

</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-SIZE:8PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;">
	(f)
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:5PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Includes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	32 stores acquired in the fiscal 2012 Acquisitions.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We plan to add approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	twenty to forty
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	new greenfield stores in fiscal 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and to pursue appropriate acquisition candidates.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Key factors in market and site selection for selecting new greenfield store locations include population, demographic characteristics, vehicle population and the intensity of competition.&nbsp;&nbsp;Monro attempts to cluster stores in market areas in order to achieve economies of scale in advertising, supervision and distribution costs.&nbsp;&nbsp;All new greenfield sites presently under consideration are within Monro's established market areas.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	As a result of extensive analysis of our historical and projected store opening strategy, we have established major market profiles, as defined by market awareness: mature, existing and new markets.&nbsp;&nbsp;Over the next several years, we expect to build a greater percentage of stores in mature and existing markets in order to capitalize on our market presence and consumer awareness.&nbsp;&nbsp;During fiscal 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	6,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	47
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	of the stores added (including acquired stores) were l
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ocated in existing markets and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	stores were added in new markets.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We believe that management and operating improvements implemented over the last several fiscal years have enhanced our ability to sustain our growth.&nbsp;&nbsp;Monro has a chain-wide computerized inventory control and electronic point-of-sale (&#x201C;POS&#x201D;) management information system, which has increased management's ability to monitor operations as the number of stores has grown.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We have customized the POS system to specific service and tire store requirements and deploy the appropriate version in each type of store.&nbsp;&nbsp;Being Windows-based, the system has simplified training of new employees. Additionally, the system includes the following:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>

<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Electronic mail and electronic cataloging, which allows store managers to electronically research the specific parts needed for the make and model of the car being serviced;

<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 13.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">

</TD>

</P>

<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The ability to view inventory of up to the closest 14 stores or warehouse; and
</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 13.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;FONT-SIZE:8PT;;">
	&#xB7;

</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Expanded monitoring of price changes. This requires more specificity on the reason for a discount, which management believes helps to control discounting.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Enhancements will continue to be made to the POS system annually in an effort to increase efficiency, improve the quality and timeliness of store reporting and enable us to better serve our customers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The financing to open a new greenfield service store location may be accomplished in one of three ways: a store lease for the land and building (in which case, land and building costs will be financed primarily by the lessor), a land lease with the building constructed by Monro (with building costs paid by Monro), or a land purchase with the building constructed by Monro.&nbsp;&nbsp;In all three cases, for service stores, each new store also will require approximatel
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	y $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	225,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	for equipment (including a POS system a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	nd a truck) and approximately $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	55,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	in inventory.&nbsp;&nbsp;Because we generally do not extend credit to our customers, stores generate almost no receivables and a new store's actual net working capital investment is nominal.&nbsp;&nbsp;Total capital required to open a new greenfield service s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	tore ranges, on average, from $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	360,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	to $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	990,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	depending on the location and which of the three financing methods is used.&nbsp;&nbsp;In general, tire stores are larger and have more service bays than Monro&#x2019;s traditional service stores and, as a result, construction costs are at the high end of the range of new store construction costs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Total capital required to open a new greenfield tire (land and building leased) location costs, on average,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	approximately $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	600,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	000, including $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	250,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	000 for equipment and $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	150,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	for inventory.&nbsp;&nbsp;In instances where Monro acquires an existing business, it may pay additional amounts for intangible assets such as customer lists, covenants not-to-compete, trade names and goodwill, but generally will pay less per bay for equipment and real property.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	At March 2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, we leased the land and/or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the building at approximately 69
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	% of our store locations and owned the land and building at the remaining locations.&nbsp;&nbsp;Monro's policy is to situate new stores in the best locations, without regard to the form of ownership required to develop the locations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	New service and tire stores, (excluding acquired stores), have a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	verage sales of approximately $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	40
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	0,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	000 and $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	1,0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	50
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, respectively, in their fir
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	st 12 months of operation, or $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	000 and $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	150,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, respectively, per bay.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	STORE OPERATIONS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Store Format
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The typical format for a Monro store is a free-standing building consisting of a sales area, fully-equipped service bays and a parts/tires storage area.&nbsp;&nbsp;Most service bays are equipped with above-ground electric vehicle lifts.&nbsp;&nbsp;Generally, each store is located within 25 miles of a &#x201C;key&#x201D; store which carries approximately double the inventory of a typical store and serves as a mini-distribution point for slower moving inventory for other stores in its area.&nbsp;&nbsp;Individual store sizes, number of bays and stocking levels vary greatly, even within the service and tire store groups, and are dependent primarily on the availability of suitable store locations, population, demographics and intensity of competition among other factors
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(See additional discussion under &#x201C;Store Additions and Closings&#x201D;).&nbsp;&nbsp;A summary of average store data for service and tire stores is presented below:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 1PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:1PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE;WIDTH: 100.00%;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;">

<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:00.84%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;HEIGHT:25.50PT;PADDING:0PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Data for the acquired ProCare service stores has been excluded because the stores&#x2019; stock rooms are smaller than those in typical service stores and therefore, they generally carry approximately half the amount of inventory of a typical service store.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Data for the Tire Warehouse and Tire Barn Warehouse stores has been excluded because these locations primarily install new tires and wheels and many perform alignments.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, most Tire Warehouse stores have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	one indoor service bay to perform alignments
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The store building houses a waiting room, storage area and an area to mount and balance tires on the car&#x2019;s wheels once the wheels and tires have been removed from the car.&nbsp;&nbsp;Removal of old tires and wheels from, and installation of new tires and wheels on, customers&#x2019; cars are performed outdoors under a carport.&nbsp;&nbsp;The average inventory carried by the Tire Warehouse and Tire
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Barn Warehouse stores is $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	251,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	per store.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stores generally are situated in high-visibility locations in suburban areas, major metropolitan areas or small towns and offer easy customer access.&nbsp;&nbsp;The typical store is open from 7:30 a.m. to 7:00 p.m. on Monday through Friday and from 7:30 a.m. to 6:00 p.m. on Saturday.&nbsp;&nbsp;A majority of store locations are also open Sundays from 9:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<A NAME="eolPage8"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A HREF="#MNRO-20160326X10K_HTM_TABLEOFCONTENTS">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Inventory Control and Management Information System
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	All Company Stores communicate daily with the central office and warehouse by computerized inventory control and electronic POS management information systems, which enable us to collect sales and operational data on a daily basis, to adjust store pricing to reflect local conditions and to control inventory on a near "real-time" basis.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, each store has access, through the POS system, to the inventory carried by up t
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	o the 14 stores o
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	r warehouse nearest to it.&nbsp;&nbsp;Management believes that this feature improves customer satisfaction and store productivity by reducing the time required to locate out-of-stock parts and tires.&nbsp;&nbsp;It also improves profitability because it reduces the amount of inventory which must be purchased outside Monro from local vendors.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Quality Control and Warranties
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	To maintain quality control, we conduct audits to rate our employees' telephone sales manner and the accuracy of pricing information given.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We have a customer survey program to monitor customer attitudes toward service quality, friendliness, speed of service, and several other factors for each store.&nbsp;&nbsp;Customer concerns are addressed by customer service and field management personnel.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Monro uses a &#x201C;Double Check for Accuracy Program&#x201D; as part of our routine store procedures.&nbsp;&nbsp;This quality assurance program requires that a technician and supervisory-level employee independently inspect a customer&#x2019;s vehicle, diagnose and document the necessary repairs, and agree on an estimate before presenting it to a customer.&nbsp;&nbsp;This process is formally documented on the written estimate by store personnel.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We are an active member of the Automotive Maintenance &amp; Repair Association (&#x201C;AMRA&#x201D;).&nbsp;&nbsp;AMRA is an organization of automotive retailers, wholesalers and manufacturers which was established as part of an industry-wide effort to address the ethics and business practices of companies in the automotive repair industry through the Motorist Assurance Program (&#x201C;MAP&#x201D;).&nbsp;&nbsp;Participating companies commit to improving consumer confidence and trust in the automotive repair industry by adopting &#x201C;Uniform Inspection Communication Standards&#x201D; (&#x201C;UICS&#x201D;) established by MAP.&nbsp;&nbsp;These &#x201C;UICS&#x201D; are available in our stores and serve to provide consistent recommendations to customers in the diagnosis and repair of a vehicle.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We offer limited warranties on substantially all of the products and services that we provide.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe that these warranties are competitive with industry practices and serve as a marketing tool to increase repeat business at our stores.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Store Personnel and Training
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Monro supervises store operations primarily through our Divisional Vice Presidents who oversee Zone Managers who, in turn, oversee Market Managers.&nbsp;&nbsp;The typical service store is staffed by a Store Manager and four to six technicians, one of whom serves as the Assistant Manager.&nbsp;&nbsp;The typical tire store, except Tire Warehouse
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and Tire Barn
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	stores, is staffed by a Store Manager, an Assistant Manager and/or Service Manager, and four to eight technicians.&nbsp;&nbsp;Larger volume service and tire stores may also have one or two sales people.&nbsp;&nbsp;The higher staffing level at many tire stores is necessary to support their higher sales volume.&nbsp;&nbsp;Tire Warehouse
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and Tire Barn
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	stores are generally staffed by a Store Manager and two to four technicians, one of whom serves as the Assistant Manager.&nbsp;&nbsp;All Store Managers receive a base salary and Assistant Managers receive either hourly or salaried compensation.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, Store Managers and Assistant Managers may receive other compensation based on their store's customer relations, gross profit, labor cost controls, safety, sales volume and other factors via a monthly or quarterly bonus based on performance in these areas.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We believe that the ability to recruit and retain qualified technicians is an important competitive factor in the automotive repair industry, which has historically experienced a high turnover rate.&nbsp;&nbsp;We make a concerted effort to recruit individuals who will have a long-term commitment to the Company and offer an hourly rate structure and additional compensation based on productivity; a competitive benefits package including health, dental, life and disability insurance; a 401(k)/profit-sharing plan; as well as the opportunity to advance within the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;Many of our Store Managers and Market Managers started with the Company as technicians.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Many of our new technicians join the Company in their early twenties as trainees or apprentices.&nbsp;&nbsp;As they progress, many are promoted to technician and eventually master technician, the latter requiring Automotive Service Excellence (&#x201C;ASE&#x201D;) certification in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	eight different categories
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;We offer a tool purchase program through which trainee technicians can acquire their own set of tools.&nbsp;&nbsp;We also will reimburse technicians for the cost of ASE certification registration fees and test fees and encourage all technicians to become certified by providing a higher hourly wage rate following their certification.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Our training program provides multiple training sessions to both Store Managers and technicians in each store, each year.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>

	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage9"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A HREF="#MNRO-20160326X10K_HTM_TABLEOFCONTENTS">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Management training courses are developed and delivered by our dedicated training department and Operations management, and are supplemented with live and on-line vendor training courses.&nbsp;&nbsp;Management training covers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	safety,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	customer service, sales, human resources (counseling, recruiting, interviewing, etc.), leadership, scheduling, financial and operational areas, and is delivered on a regular basis.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe that involving Operations management in the development and delivery of these sessions results in more relevant and actionable training for Store Managers, and helps to improve overall performance and staff retention.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Our training department develops and coordinates technical training courses on critical areas of automotive repair to Monro technicians (e.g. Antilock braking systems (&#x201C;ABS&#x201D;) brake repair, drivability, tire pressure monitoring system (&#x201C;TPMS&#x201D;), etc.) and also conducts required technical training to maintain compliance with state inspection licenses, where applicable, and AMRA/MAP accreditation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, our training department holds periodic field technical clinics for store personnel and coordinates technician attendance at technical clinics offered by our vendors.&nbsp;&nbsp;We have electronic repair manuals installed in all of our stores for daily reference.&nbsp;&nbsp;We also issue technical bulletins to all stores on innovative or complex repair processes, and maintain a centralized database for technical repair problems.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, Monro has established a telephone technical help line to provide assistance to store personnel in resolving problems encountered while diagnosing and repairing vehicles.&nbsp;&nbsp;The help line is available during all hours of store operation.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Monro also maintains an employee website that contains many resources for both managers and technicians to reference including Human Resource information and forms.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, there is a Facilities section containing important environmental and equipment information, as well as a Training section that contains training programs and documents for both managers and technicians.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	OPERATING STRATEGY
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Monro's operating strategy is to provide our customers with a wide range of dependable, high-quality automotive services at a competitive price by emphasizing the following key elements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Products and Services
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The typical store provides a full range of undercar repair services for brakes, steering, mufflers and exhaust systems, drive train, suspension and wheel alignment, as well as tire replacement and service.&nbsp;&nbsp;These services apply to all makes and models of domestic and foreign cars, light trucks and vans.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a percentage of sales, the service stores provide significantly more brake and exhaust service
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	than tire stores, and tire stores provide substantially more tire replacement and related services than service stores.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Stores generally provide many of the routine maintenance services (except engine diagnostic), which automobile manufacturers suggest or require in the vehicle owner&#x2019;s manuals, and which fulfill manufacturers&#x2019; requirements for new car warranty compliance.&nbsp;&nbsp;We offer "Scheduled Maintenance" services in our stores whereby the aforementioned services are packaged and offered to consumers based upon the year, make, model and mileage of each specific vehicle.&nbsp;&nbsp;Management believes that we are able to offer this service in a more convenient and cost competitive fashion than auto dealers can provide.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Included in maintenance services are oil change services, heating and cooling system "flush and fill" service, belt installation, fuel system service and a transmission "flush and fill" service.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, most stores replace and service batteries, starters and alternators.&nbsp;&nbsp;Stores in Georgia, Maine, Maryland,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Massachusetts,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Missouri, New Hampshire, New York, North Carolina, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, Vermont, Virginia, West Virginia and Wisconsin perform annual sta
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	te inspections.&nbsp;&nbsp;Approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	63
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	% of our stores also offer air conditioning services.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	The format of the Tire Warehouse
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and Tire Barn Warehouse stores
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	are slightly different from Monro&#x2019;s typical service or tire stores (as described a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	bove) in that, generally, over
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	% of the stores&#x2019; sales involve tire services, including the mounting and balancing of tires, and the sale of road hazard warranties.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Most of these
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	stores
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	also
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	provide the installatio
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	n of wiper blades.&nbsp;&nbsp;Currently,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	70% of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Tire Warehouse and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	87% of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Tire Barn Warehouse stores perform alignments.&nbsp;&nbsp;In fiscal year 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, Monro plans to expand the number of Tire Warehouse and Tire Barn Warehouse stores offering alignme
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	nt services to 83% of total

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	stores.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Centralized Control
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	While we both operate and franchise stores, we believe that direct operation of stores enhances our ability to compete by providing centralized control of such areas of operations as service quality, store appearance, promotional activity and pricing.&nbsp;&nbsp;We
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	also
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	believe our experience in operating stores makes us a more valuable partner to our franchisees.&nbsp;&nbsp;A high level of competence is maintained throughout the Company, as we require, as a condition of employment, that employees participate in periodic training programs, including sales, management, customer service and changes in automotive technology.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, purchasing, distribution, merchandising, advertising, accounting and other store support functions are centralized primarily in Monro's corporate headquarters in Rochester, New York, and are provided through our subsidiary, Monro Service Corporation.&nbsp;&nbsp;The centralization of these functions results in efficiencies and gives management the ability to closely monitor and control costs.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	&nbsp;
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Most parts are shipped by vendors to our primary warehouse facility in Rochester, New York, and are distributed to stores by the Monro-operated tractor/trailer fleet.&nbsp;&nbsp;The majority of tires are shipped to our stores directly by vendors pursuant to orders placed by our headquarters staff.&nbsp;&nbsp;During fiscal 2013, we completed an expansion of our Rochester warehouse from 80,000 square feet to 135,000 square feet.&nbsp;&nbsp;Stores are replenished at least bi-weekly from this warehouse, and such re
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	plenishment fills, on average,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	97
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	% of all items ordered by the stores' automatic POS-driven replenishment system.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Rochester wa
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	rehouse stocks approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	3,7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	00 SKUs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Monro also operates warehouses in Maryland, Virginia, New Hampshire and Kentucky.&nbsp;&nbsp;These
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	warehouses carry, on average, 1,100; 2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	00;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	00 and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	00 SKUs, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We enter into contracts with certain parts and tire suppliers, some of which require us t
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	o buy (at market prices) up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	0% of our annual purchases of specific products.&nbsp;&nbsp;These agreements expire at various dates through July 2017.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe these agreements provide us with high quality, branded merchandise at preferred pricing, along with strong marketing and training support.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	COMPETITION
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Monro competes in the retail automotive service and tire industry.&nbsp;&nbsp;This industry is generally highly competitive and fragmented, and the number, size and strength of competitors vary widely from region to region.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe that competition in this industry is based on customer service and reputation, store location, name awareness and price.&nbsp;&nbsp;Monro's primary competitors include national and regional undercar, tire specialty and general automotive service chains, both franchised and company-operated; car dealerships, mass merchandisers&#x2019; operating service centers; and, to a lesser extent, gas stations, independent garages and Internet tire sellers.&nbsp;&nbsp;Monro considers TBC Corporation (operating under the NTB, Merchant&#x2019;s Tire, Midas and Tire Kingdom brands), Firestone Complete Auto Care service stores and Meineke Discount Mufflers Inc. to be direct competitors.&nbsp;&nbsp;In most of the new markets that we have entered, at least one competitor was already present.&nbsp;&nbsp;In identifying new markets, we analyze, among other factors, the intensity of competition.&nbsp;&nbsp;(See "Expansion Strategy&#x201D; and &#x201C;Management&#x2019;s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations".)
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	EMPLOYEES
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	As of March 2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6, Monro had
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6,725
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	employees, of whom
</FONT>

	6,347
</FONT>

	were emplo
</FONT>

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	&#xFEFF;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	REGULATION
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We are subject to various federal, state and local laws and governmental regulations relating to the operation of our business, including those governing workplace safety, zoning and the handling, storage and disposal of hazardous substances contained in the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	products
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	that we sell and use in our service bays, the recycling of batteries, tires and used lubricants, and the ownership and operation of real property.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;We maintain programs to facilitate compliance with these laws and regulations.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe that we are in substantial compliance with all applicable environmental and other laws and regulations
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and that the cost of such compliance is not material to the Company.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Monro stores new oil and recycled antifreeze and generates and/or handles used tires and automotive oils, antifreeze and certain solvents, which are disposed of by licensed third-party contractors.&nbsp;&nbsp;In certain states, as required, we also recycle oil filters.&nbsp;&nbsp;Thus, we are subject to a number of federal, state and local environmental laws including the Comprehensive Environmental Response Compensation and Liability Act (&#x201C;CERCLA&#x201D;).&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, the United States Environmental Protection Agency (the "EPA"), under the Resource Conservation and Recovery Act ("RCRA"), and various state and local environmental protection agencies regulate our handling and disposal of waste.&nbsp;&nbsp;The EPA, under the Clean Air Act, also regulates the installation of catalytic converters by Monro and all other repair stores by periodically spot checking repair jobs, and has the power to fine businesses that use improper procedures or materials.&nbsp;&nbsp;The EPA has the authority to impose sanctions, including civil penalties up
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	to $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	37,5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	00 per violation (or up to $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	37,5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	00
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	per day for certain willful violations or failures to cooperate with authorities), for violations of RCRA and the Clean Air Act.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Monro is environmentally conscious, and takes advantage of recycling opportunities at our offices, warehouses and stores.&nbsp;&nbsp;Cardboard, plastic shrink wrap and parts&#x2019; cores are returned to the warehouse by the stores on Monro stock trucks.&nbsp;&nbsp;There, they are accumulated for sale to recycling companies or returned to parts manufacturers for credit.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	SEASONALITY
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Although our business is not highly seasonal, customers do purchase more undercar service during the period of March through October than the period of November through February, when miles driven tend to be lower.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the tire stores, the better sales months are typically May through August, and October through December.&nbsp;&nbsp;The slowest months are typically January through April and September.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a result, profitability is typically lower during slower sales months, or months where mix is more heavily weighted toward tires, which is a lower margin category.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, since our stores are primarily located in the northeastern and midwestern United States, profitability tends to be lower in the winter months when certain costs, such as utilities and snow plowing, are typically higher.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>

<EFX_RISK_FACTORS>
<A NAME="FIS_RISK_FACTORS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A NAME="MNRO-20160326X10K_HTM__TOC79382287">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Ite
</FONT>
<A NAME="MNRO-20160326X10K_HTM_RISKFACTORS">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	m 1A.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Risk Factors
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In addition to the risks discussed elsewhere in this annual report, the following are the important factors that could cause Monro&#x2019;s actual results to differ materially from those projected in any forward looking statements:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We operate in the highly competitive automotive repair industry.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The automotive repair industry in which we operate is generally highly competitive and fragmented, and the number, size and strength of our competitors varies widely from region to region.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe that competition in the industry is based primarily on customer service, reputation, store location, name awareness and price.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our primary competitors include national and regional undercar, tire specialty and general automotive service chains, both franchised and company-operated, car dealerships, mass merchandisers&#x2019; operating service centers and, to a lesser extent, gas stations, independent garages and Internet tire sellers.&nbsp;&nbsp;Some of our competitors have greater financial resources, are more geographically diverse and have better name recognition than we do, which might place us at a competitive disadvantage to those competitors.&nbsp;&nbsp;Because we seek to offer competitive prices, if our competitors reduce prices, we may be forced to reduce our prices, which could have a material adverse effect on our business, financial condition and results of operations.&nbsp;&nbsp;Further, our success within this industry also depends upon our ability to respond in a timely manner to changes in customer demands for both products and services.&nbsp;&nbsp;We cannot assure that we, or any of our stores, will be able to compete effectively.&nbsp;&nbsp;If we are unable to compete successfully in new and existing markets, we may not achieve our projected revenue and profitability targets.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We are subject to seasonality and cycles in the general economy and customers&#x2019; use of vehicles, which may impact demand for our products and services.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Although our business is not highly seasonal, our customers typically purchase more undercar services during the period of March through October than the period of November through February, when miles driven tend to be lower. Further, customers may defer or forego vehicle maintenance at any time during periods of inclement weather. In the tire stores, the better sales months are typically May through August, and October through December. The slowest months are typically January through April and September. As a result, profitability is typically lower during slower sales months, or months where mix is more heavily weighted toward tires, which is a lower margin category.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Additionally, since our stores are primarily located in the northeastern
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and midwestern
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	United States, profitability tends to be lower in the winter months when certain costs, such as utilities and snow plowing, are typically higher.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The automotive repair industry is subject to fluctuations in the general economy. During a downturn in the economy, customers may defer or forego vehicle maintenance or repair. During periods of good economic conditions, consumers may decide to purchase new vehicles rather than having their older vehicles serviced.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Further, our industry is influenced by the number of miles driven by automobile owners.&nbsp;&nbsp;Factors that may cause the number of miles driven by automobile owners to decrease include the weather, travel patterns, gas prices and, as discussed above, fluctuations in the general economy.&nbsp;&nbsp;Should a significant reduction in the number of miles driven by automobile owners occur, it would likely have an adverse effect on the demand for our products and services. For example, when the retail cost of gasoline increases, the number of miles driven by automobile owners may decrease, which could result in less frequent service intervals and fewer repairs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Accordingly, a significant reduction in the number of miles driven by automobile owners could have a material adverse effect on our business and results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We depend on our relationships with our vendors, including foreign sources, for certain inventory.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our business may be negatively affected by the risks associated with such relationships and international trade.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We depend on close relationships with our vendors for parts, tires and supplies and for our ability to purchase products at competitive prices and terms.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our ability to purchase at competitive prices and terms results from the volume of our purchases from these vendors.&nbsp;&nbsp;We have entered into various contracts with parts suppliers that require us to buy from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	them (at market prices) up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	00% of our annual purchases of specific products.&nbsp;&nbsp;These agreements expire at various dates through
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	July 2017
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	12

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We believe that alternative sources exist for most of the products we sell or use at our stores, and we would not expect the loss of any one supplier to have a material adverse effect on our business, financial condition or results of operations.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our dependence on a small number of suppliers, however, subjects us to the risks of shortages and interruptions.&nbsp;&nbsp;If any of our suppliers do not perform adequately or otherwise fail to distribute parts or other supplies to our stores, our inability to replace the suppliers in a timely manner and on acceptable terms could increase our costs and could cause shortages or interruptions that could have a material adverse effect on our business, financial condition and results of operations.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Further, we depend on a number of products (e.g. brake parts, tires, oil filters) produced in foreign markets. We face risks associated with the delivery of inventory originating outside the United States, including:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	potential economic and political instability in countries where our suppliers are located;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our industry is subject to environmental, consumer protection and other regulation.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We are subject to various federal, state and local environmental laws, building and zoning requirements, employment laws and other governmental regulations regarding the operation of our business.&nbsp;&nbsp;For example, we are subject to rules governing the handling, storage and disposal of hazardous substances contained in some of the products such as motor oil that we sell and use at our stores, the recycling of batteries, tires and used lubricants, and the ownership and operation of real property.&nbsp;&nbsp;These laws and regulations can impose fines and criminal sanctions for violations and require the installation of pollution control equipment or operational changes to decrease the likelihood of accidental hazardous substance releases.&nbsp;&nbsp;Accordingly, we could become subject to material liabilities relating to the investigation and cleanup of contaminated properties, and to claims alleging personal injury or property damage as a result of exposure to, or release of, hazardous substances.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, stricter interpretation of existing laws and regulations, new laws and regulations, the discovery of previously unknown contamination or the imposition of new or increased requirements could require us to incur costs or become the basis of new or increased liabilities that could have a material adverse effect on our business, financial condition and results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	National automotive repair chains have also been the subject of investigations and reports by consumer protection agencies and the Attorneys General of various states.&nbsp;&nbsp;Publicity in connection with these kinds of investigations could have an adverse effect on our sales and, consequently, our business, financial condition and results of operations.&nbsp;&nbsp;State and local governments have also enacted numerous consumer protection laws with which we must comply.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The costs of operating our stores may increase if there are changes in laws governing minimum hourly wages, working conditions, overtime, workers&#x2019; compensation and health insurance rates, unemployment tax rates or other laws and regulations.&nbsp;&nbsp;A material increase in these costs that we were unable to offset by increasing our prices or by other means could have a material adverse effect on our business, financial condition and results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	We are involved in litigation from time to time arising from the operation of our business and, as such, we could incur substantial judgments, fines, legal fees or other costs.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We are sometimes the subject of complaints or litigation from customers, employees or other third parties for various actions.&nbsp;&nbsp;From time to time, we are involved in litigation involving claims related to, among other things, breach of contract, negligence, tortious conduct and employment law matters, including payment of wages.&nbsp;&nbsp;The damages sought against us in some of these litigation proceedings could be substantial.&nbsp;&nbsp;Although we maintain liability insurance for some litigation claims, if one or more of the claims were to greatly exceed our insurance coverage limits or if our insurance policies do not cover a claim, this could have a material adverse effect on our business, financial condition, results of operations and cash flows.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
