<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	171,0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	00
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	145

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,000
</FONT>

	and

	91
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	of stock options, respectively, as the exercise price of these options was greater than the average market value of Monro&#x2019;s Common Stock for those periods, resulting in an anti-dilutive effect on diluted earnings per share.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:14PT;">
	MONRO MUFFLER BRAKE, INC. AND SUBSIDIARIES
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	NOTE 11 &#x2013; OPERATING LEASES AND OTHER COMMITMENTS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We lease retail facilities under noncancellable lease agreements which expire a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	t various dates through fiscal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	204
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition to stated minimum payments, certain real estate leases have provisions for contingent rentals when retail sales exceed specified levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;Generally, the leases provide for renewal for various periods at stipulated rates.&nbsp;&nbsp;Most of the facilities&#x2019; leases require payment of property taxes, insurance and maintenance costs in addition to rental payments, and several provide an option to purchase the property at the end of the lease term.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In recent years, we have entered into agreements for the sale/leaseback of certain stores.&nbsp;&nbsp;Realized gains are deferred and are credited to income as rent expense adjustments over the lease terms.&nbsp;&nbsp;We have lease renewal options under the real estate agreements at projected future fair market values.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Future minimum payments required under noncancellable leases (including closed stores) are as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 1PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:1PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$420,000

	$60,000

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the Company

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	use the funds made available by such reduction to provide assistance to Monro employees facing financial hardships.&nbsp;&nbsp;No other changes to Mr.&nbsp;Gross&#x2019; compensation were made.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr.&nbsp;Gross&#x2019; new annual salary of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$360,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	was effective beginning October&nbsp;1, 2014.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	NOTE 12 &#x2013; EMPLOYEE RETIREMENT AND PROFIT SHARING PLANS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We sponsor a noncontributory defined benefit pension plan for Monro employees and the former Kimmel Automotive, Inc. employees.&nbsp;&nbsp;In fiscal 2005, the previously separate Monro and Kimmel pension plans were merged.&nbsp;&nbsp;The merged plan provides benefits to certain full-time employees who were employed with Monro and with Kimmel prior to April 2, 1998 and May 15, 2001, respectively.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Effective as of those dates, each company&#x2019;s Board of Directors approved plan amendments whereby the benefits of each of the defined benefit plans would be frozen and the plans would be closed to new participants.&nbsp;&nbsp;Prior to these amendments, coverage under the plans began after employees completed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	year of service and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	attained
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	age
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	21
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Benefits under both plans, and now the merged plan, are based primarily on years of service and employees&#x2019; pay near retirement.&nbsp;&nbsp;The funding policy for Monro&#x2019;s merged plan is consistent with the funding requirements of Federal law and regulations.&nbsp;&nbsp;The measurement date used to determine the pension plan measurements disclosed herein is March 31 for both 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	underfunded
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	status of Monro&#x2019;s defined benefit plan is recognized as
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	an other long-term l
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	iability
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the Consolidated Balance Sheets as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	March 26, 2016 and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	March 28, 2015, respectively.

</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The investment strategy of the plan is to conservatively manage the assets in order to meet the plan&#x2019;s long-term obligations while maintaining sufficient liquidity to pay current benefits.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is achieved by holding equity investments while investing a portion of assets in long duration bonds to match the long-term nature of the liabilities.&nbsp;&nbsp;Monro&#x2019;s general target allocation for the plan is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	40%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fixed income and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	60%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	equity securities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Monro&#x2019;s asset allocations, by asset category, are as follows at the end of each year:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 1PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:1PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	A financial instrument&#x2019;s level within the fair value hierarchy is based on the lowest level of any input that is significant to the fair value measurement.
</FONT>

	&nbsp;The following table provides fair value measurement information for Monro&#x2019;s major categories of defined benefit plan assets at
</FONT>

	, 2016 and

	We have a 401(k)/Profit Sharing Plan that covers full-time employees who meet the age and service requirements of the plan.&nbsp;&nbsp;The 401(k) salary deferral option was added to the plan during fiscal 2000.&nbsp;&nbsp;The first employee deferral occurred in March 2000.&nbsp;&nbsp;We make matching contributions consistent with the provisions of the plan.&nbsp;&nbsp;Charges to expense for our matchi

	ng contributions for fiscal 2016, 2015 and 2014

	,000

	, respectively.&nbsp;&nbsp;We may also make annual profit sharing contributions to the plan at the discretion of Monro&#x2019;s Compensation Committee.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We have a deferred compensation plan (the &#x201C;Deferred Compensation Plan&#x201D;) to provide an opportunity for additional tax-deferred savings to a select group of management or highly compensated employees.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Deferred Compensation Plan permits participants to defer all or any portion of the compensation that would otherwise be payable to them for the calendar year.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, Monro will credit to the participants&#x2019; accounts such amounts as would have been contributed to Monro&#x2019;s 401(k)/Profit Sharing Plan but for the limitations that are imposed under the Internal Revenue Code based upon the participants&#x2019; status as highly compensated employees.&nbsp;&nbsp;We may also make such additional discretionary allocations as are determined by the Compensation Committee.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Deferred Compensation Plan is an unfunded arrangement and the participants or their beneficiaries have an unsecured claim against the general assets of Monro to the extent of their Deferred Compensation Plan benefits.&nbsp;&nbsp;We maintain accounts to reflect the amounts owed to each participant.&nbsp;&nbsp;At least annually, the accounts are credited with earnings or losses calculated on the basis of an interest rate or other formula as determined by Monro&#x2019;s Compensation Committee.&nbsp;&nbsp;The total liability recorded in our financial statements at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	March 26, 2016 and March 28, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	related to the Deferred Compensation Plan was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$1,921,0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	00
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$1,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	678
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,000

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, respectively.

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	will record the amount of the loss, or the minimum estimated liability when the loss is estimated using a range, and no point within the range is more probable than another. As additional information becomes available, any potential liability related to these matters is assessed and the estimates are revised, if necessary.&nbsp;&nbsp;Litigation is subject to inherent uncertainties, and unfavorable rulings could occur and may include monetary damages.&nbsp;&nbsp;If an unfavorable ruling were to occur, there exists the possibility of a material adverse impact on the financial position and results of operations of the period in which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	any such
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ruling occurs, or in future periods.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, based on currently available information, management believes that the ultimate outcome of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	any of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	these matters, individually and in the aggregate, will not have a material adverse effect on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	financial position
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	overall trends in results of operations
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	or cash flow
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<EFX_CONTROL_AND_PROCEDURES>
<A NAME="FIS_CONTROL_AND_PROCEDURES"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	It
</FONT>
<A NAME="MNRO-20160326X10K_HTM_CONTROLSANDPROCEDURES">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	em 9A.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Controls and Procedures
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Evaluation of Disclosure Controls and Procedures
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We maintain disclosure controls and procedures that are designed to ensure that information required to be disclosed in reports that we file or submit pursuant to the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 is recorded, processed, summarized and reported within the time periods specified in the Securities and Exchange Commission&#x2019;s (SEC) rules and forms, and that such information is accumulated and communicated to Monro&#x2019;s management, including its Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer, as appropriate, to allow timely decisions regarding required disclosure.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In conjunction with the close of each fiscal quarter and under the supervision of our Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer, we conduct an evaluation of the effectiveness of our disclosure controls and procedures.&nbsp;&nbsp;It is the conclusion of Monro&#x2019;s Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer, based upon an evaluation completed as of March 2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, that our disclosure controls and procedures were effective in ensuring that any material information relating to Monro was recorded, processed, summarized and reported to its principal officers to allow timely decisions regarding required disclosures.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Management's Report on Internal Control over Financial Reporting
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Management is responsible for establishing and maintaining adequate internal control over financial reporting.&nbsp;&nbsp;Monro&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting is a process designed to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external reporting purposes in accordance with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States of America.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Monro&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting includes those policies and procedures that (i) pertain to the maintenance of records that, in reasonable detail, accurately and fairly reflect the transactions and dispositions of the assets of Monro; (ii) provide reasonable assurance that transactions are recorded as necessary to permit preparation of financial statements in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles, and that receipts and expenditures of Monro are being made only in accordance with authorizations of management and directors of Monro; and (iii) provide reasonable assurance regarding prevention or timely detection of unauthorized acquisition, use, or disposition of Monro's assets that could have a material effect on the financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Management conducted an evaluation of the effectiveness of internal control over financial reporting based on the framework in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Internal Control - Integrated Framework (2013)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	issued by the Committee of Sponsoring Organizations of the Treadway Commission.&nbsp;&nbsp;Based on this evaluation, management concluded that Monro's internal control over financial reporting was effective as of March
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	26
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, the end of our fiscal year.&nbsp;&nbsp;Management has reviewed the results of its assessment with the Audit Committee of the Board of Directors.&nbsp;&nbsp;The effectiveness of Monro's internal control over financial reporting as of March 2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	has been audited by PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP, an independent registered public accounting firm, as stated in their report which appears herein.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Inherent Limitations on Effectiveness of Controls
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Monro&#x2019;s management, including its Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer, does not expect that its disclosure controls and procedures or its internal control over financial reporting will prevent or detect all errors and all fraud.&nbsp;&nbsp;A control system, no matter how well designed and operated, can provide only reasonable, not absolute, assurance that the control system&#x2019;s objectives will be met.&nbsp;&nbsp;The design of a control system must reflect the fact that there are resource constraints, and the benefits of controls must be considered relative to their costs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Further, because of the inherent limitations in all control systems, no evaluation of controls can provide absolute assurance that misstatements due to error or fraud will not occur or that all control issues and instances of fraud, if any, within Monro have been detected.&nbsp;&nbsp;These inherent limitations include the realities that judgments in decision-making can be faulty and that breakdowns can occur because of simple error or mistake.&nbsp;&nbsp;Controls can also be circumvented by the individual acts of some persons, by collusion of two or more people, or by management override of the controls.&nbsp;&nbsp;The design of any system of controls is based in part on certain assumptions about the likelihood of future events, and there can be no assurance that any design will succeed in achieving its stated goals under all potential future conditions.&nbsp;&nbsp;Projections of any evaluation of controls&#x2019; effectiveness to future periods are subject to risks.&nbsp;&nbsp;Over time, controls may become inadequate because of changes in conditions or deterioration in the degree of compliance with policies or procedures.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	There were no changes in Monro&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting during the quarter ended March 2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	that materially affected, or are reasonably likely to materially affect, Monro&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting.
</FONT>
</P>

</FONT>

	s

	captioned

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Compensation&#x201D; in the Proxy Statement.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

<A NAME="FIS_POWER_OF_ATTORNEY"></A>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	POWER OF ATTORNEY
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:CG TIMES (WN);FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:CG TIMES (WN);FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:CG TIMES (WN);TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	KNOW ALL PERSONS BY THESE PRESENTS, that the undersigned directors of Monro Muffler Brake, Inc., a New York corporation (the "Corporation"), do constitute and appoint JOHN W. VAN HEEL to be their true and lawful attorney-in-fact and agent, with full powers of substitution, for and in the name, place and stead of the undersigned, in any and all capacities in connection with the filing of the Annual Report on Form 10-K of the Corporation for the fiscal year ended March 26, 2016 (the "Form 10-K") with the Securities and Exchange Commission, to sign the Form 10-K and any and all amendments related thereto and to file the same, with any exhibits thereto, and other documents in connection therewith, with the Securities and Exchange Commission, granting unto said attorney-in-fact and agent, or his substitutes, full power and authority to do and perform each and every act and thing requisite and necessary to be done for all intents and purposes as the undersigned might or could do in person, hereby ratifying and confirming all that said attorney-in-fact and agent, or his substitutes, may lawfully do or cause to be done by virtue hereof.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:CG TIMES (WN);FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>

</FONT>

</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

	Based on my knowledge, the financial statements, and other financial information included in this report, fairly present in all material respects the financial condition, results of operations and cash flows of the registrant as of, and for, the periods presented in this report;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

</TD>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	4.

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The registrant's other certifying officer and I are responsible for establishing and maintaining disclosure controls and procedures (as defined in Exchange Act Rules 13a-15(e) and 15d-15(e)) and internal control over financial reporting (as defined in Exchange Act Rules 13a-15(f) and 15d-15(f))&nbsp;&nbsp;for the registrant and have:
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(a) Designed such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused such disclosure controls and procedures to be designed under our supervision, to ensure that material information relating to the registrant, including its consolidated subsidiary, is made known to us by others within those entities, particularly during the period in which this report is being prepared;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(b) Designed such internal control over financial reporting, or caused such internal control over financial reporting to be designed under our supervision, to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(c) Evaluated the effectiveness of the registrant&#x2019;s disclosure controls and procedures and presented in this report our conclusions about the effectiveness of the disclosure controls and procedures, as of the end of the period covered by this report based on such evaluation; and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(d) Disclosed in this report any change in the registrant&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting that occurred during the registrant&#x2019;s most recent fiscal quarter (the registrant&#x2019;s fourth fiscal quarter in the case of an annual report) that has materially affected, or is reasonably likely to materially affect, the registrant&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting; and
</FONT>
</P>

	The registrant&#x2019;s other certifying officer and I have disclosed, based on our most recent evaluation of internal control over financial reporting, to the registrant&#x2019;s auditors and the audit committee of the registrant&#x2019;s board of directors (or persons performing the equivalent functions):
